  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">You have become adept at drawing in ether from other creatures and the recently departed, making use of the power within while it retains its strongest potency. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.actions.Item.1ATKSEf1zPBfGODM]{Draw Soul} free action.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">When you acquire a mote of ether from Drain Ether or Draw Soul, instead of immediately using it, you can stow it within you instead as a free action. Once stowed, you can later choose to use it as normal as a single Interact action. Alternatively, when you Cast a Spell using focus points, you can choose to make use of the stowed mote to negate up to 2 points of the focus point cost to cast the spell. You can only stow one mote at a time, and the mote dissipates after ten minutes.</span></p>"
